{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-05T18:28:01.217Z","question":"Scope: which aggregates/entities are in the core model? Proposed Plan, Subscription, Invoice, UsageRecord","answer":"Drop UsageRecord: usage arrives as a pre-aggregated counter on Subscription; individual usage events out of scope. Keep Plan, Subscription, Invoice."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-05T18:31:07.280Z","question":"Subscription lifecycle states?","answer":"As proposed: trialing (initial), active(@active), past_due(@active), canceled(@terminal), expired(@terminal). Dunning covered via past_due."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-05T18:32:25.653Z","question":"Invoice machine shape and partial payments?","answer":"draft -> open -> paid(@terminal) / void(@terminal) PLUS uncollectible(@terminal) for written-off invoices. Partial payments representable: amountPaid Money @balance accrues; paid requires amountPaid >= totalDue."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-05T18:33:48.465Z","question":"How do license fee and usage charge combine on an invoice?","answer":"Both modes supported per plan: per-seat license fee (plan.licenseFee x subscription.seats) plus EITHER overage usage (usageRate x max(0, accruedUnits - includedUnits)) OR all-usage (usageRate x accruedUnits). Plan gets a UsagePricing enum: overage | all_units; includedUnits applies in overage mode."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-05T18:35:13.057Z","question":"Which transitions, and from which states can cancel be invoked?","answer":"activate trialing->active; expire_trial trialing->expired; payment_failed active->past_due; recover past_due->active; cancel from trialing, active, and past_due -> canceled. Also dunning exhaustion: past_due -> expired."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-05T18:36:49.148Z","question":"Correction: dunning exhaustion exit from past_due?","answer":"past_due -> canceled (dunning_exhausted transition), NOT past_due -> expired. expired is reserved for unconverted trials. This corrects the previous ledger entry's 'past_due -> expired' note."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-05T18:37:50.379Z","question":"accruedUnits semantics: lifetime cumulative vs per-period reset?","answer":"Per-period: accruedUnits resets to 0 at period rollover. Drop @monotonic tag (within-period monotonicity can be elicited as an invariant later, not template-adopted)."}
