{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-08T22:34:09.367Z","question":"activate (trialing->active) guard: what fact must hold before a subscription can leave trialing? b03's shape assumes a payment fact — is a raw invoice-count field enough, or do we need the pre-aggregated-counter pattern?","answer":"Add field paidInvoiceCount : Int to Subscription (pre-aggregated-counter pattern, consistent with accruedUnits). activate requires paidInvoiceCount >= 1."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-08T22:34:17.231Z","question":"dunning/b10: dunningExhausted (pastDue->canceled) needs a retry-cap guard per b10's template shape. Whose field is the retry counter — Subscription's or Invoice's? And should the cap be a transition GUARD (blocking the transition) or a coupling INVARIANT?","answer":"Retries belong to Invoice (the domain truth: retries are attempts to collect a specific invoice, not a subscription-level fact). Add retryCount : Int to Invoice, maxRetries : Int to Subscription, and latestInvoice : ref Invoice to Subscription so Subscription can reach the invoice. dunningExhausted stays UNGUARDED (no requires clause) — the retry cap is expressed instead as a coupling invariant: invariant retryCapWhilePastDue where state status in {pastDue} { latestInvoice.retryCount <= maxRetries }."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-08T22:34:24.821Z","question":"TRANSLATOR-ASKED BOUNDARY (declined path): could the retry cap and the b03 paid-in-full rule instead be expressed as CROSS-AGGREGATE transition GUARDS (e.g. dunningExhausted requires latestInvoice.retryCount <= maxRetries directly on the transition), with a 'latest of list' selector picking the most recent invoice from a collection?","answer":"DECLINED for v1. Cross-aggregate transition guards (requires reaching through a ref into another aggregate's fields) and latest-of-list selectors are explicitly out of scope for v1 per the engine's grammar (transition/method requires is strictly own-field, single-segment only — see checkScopedPred/guard-cross-aggregate). Accepted the invariant form instead: both rules land as coupling INVARIANTS (retryCapWhilePastDue, activePaidInFull) which the engine supports via same-context ref-hop paths in invariant bodies (resolveFieldPath), not as guards."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-08T22:34:30.776Z","question":"b03 companion: activate's guard (paidInvoiceCount >= 1) only checks that at least one invoice was ever paid — should there also be a rule that an ACTIVE subscription's current invoice is paid in full?","answer":"Yes: invariant activePaidInFull where state status in {active} { latestInvoice.amountPaid == latestInvoice.totalDue }. This is a coupling invariant (ref-hop through latestInvoice), companion to the b03 activate guard."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-08T22:34:36.523Z","question":"Invoice guards: settle (open->paid) and finalize (draft->open) currently have no requires clause. What should gate each?","answer":"settle { from open to paid; requires amountPaid == totalDue }. finalize { from draft to open; requires totalDue == licenseFeeAmount + usageAmount }. Both are own-field-only guards on Invoice."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-08T22:34:43.590Z","question":"The multi-source cancel: today cancelFromTrial (trialing->canceled), cancelFromActive (active->canceled), and cancelFromPastDue (pastDue->canceled) are three separate transitions. Given the grammar now supports a single transition with multiple 'from' states, should these collapse into one?","answer":"Yes: replace all three with ONE transition cancel { from trialing, active, pastDue to canceled; emits SubscriptionCanceled }. This is a ledger-referenced rename set (three transitions removed, one added) — apply via engine apply, expect structuralNotes to show removed+added transitions rather than a clean rename, which is acceptable."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-08T22:34:49.082Z","question":"Which transitions should announce domain events, and what should the events be named/shaped?","answer":"Four events, each with an id field: SubscriptionActivated { subId : Id } emitted by activate; SubscriptionCanceled { subId : Id } emitted by cancel; InvoicePaid { invoiceId : Id } emitted by settle; InvoiceFinalized { invoiceId : Id } emitted by finalize."}
{"kind":"structure","at":"2026-07-08T22:34:54.724Z","question":"Service seeding: which transitions are operations someone (a caller) invokes, and what's the service surface?","answer":"service SubscriptionService { createSubscription(plan: ref Catalog.Plan, seats: Int): Subscription creates Subscription; getSubscription(subId: Id): Subscription read-only; activate(subId: Id) performs Subscription.activate; cancel(subId: Id) performs Subscription.cancel }. (If ref Catalog.Plan does not validate as a method param type, substitute planId: Id and note the substitution.)"}
{"kind":"adopted","at":"2026-07-08T22:45:12.463Z","invariant":{"id":"hand-activePaidInFull","name":"activePaidInFull","prior":1,"source":"template","candidate":{"kind":"statePredicate","aggregate":"Subscription","body":{"kind":"cmp","op":"eq","left":{"kind":"field","owner":"self","path":["latestInvoice","amountPaid"]},"right":{"kind":"field","owner":"self","path":["latestInvoice","totalDue"]}},"where":{"kind":"inState","owner":"self","region":"status","states":["active"]}},"doc":"An active subscription's current invoice is paid in full (companion to the activate guard)."},"provenance":"hand-edited 2026-07-08, consistent with w1, w2, w3, w4, w5"}
{"kind":"adopted","at":"2026-07-08T22:45:12.463Z","invariant":{"id":"hand-retryCapWhilePastDue","name":"retryCapWhilePastDue","prior":1,"source":"template","candidate":{"kind":"statePredicate","aggregate":"Subscription","body":{"kind":"cmp","op":"le","left":{"kind":"field","owner":"self","path":["latestInvoice","retryCount"]},"right":{"kind":"field","owner":"self","path":["maxRetries"]}},"where":{"kind":"inState","owner":"self","region":"status","states":["pastDue"]}},"doc":"While past due, dunning retries on the current invoice never exceed the subscription's cap."},"provenance":"hand-edited 2026-07-08, consistent with w1, w2, w3, w4, w5"}
